%2Fwe-moved-to-canada-not-perfect-but-prefer-over-us-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20to%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20spike%20after%20big%20political%20events%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftrends.google.com%2Ftrends%2Fexplore%3Fdate%3D2016-11-01%25202016-11-30%26geo%3DUS%26q%3Dmoving%2520to%2520canada%26hl%3Den-US%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2016%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftrends.google.com%2Ftrends%2Fexplore%3Fdate%3D2022-06-01%25202022-06-30%26geo%3DUS%26q%3Dmoving%2520to%2520canada%26hl%3Den-US%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverturning%20of%20the%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%3C%2Fa%3E%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20phenomenon%20doesn't%20just%20live%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20either%20%E2%80%94%20some%20US%20residents%20are%20seriously%20considering%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20when%20Trump%20was%20elected%20last%20time%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20felt%20that%20they%20weren't%20as%20comfortable%20staying%20in%20the%20States%2C%20and%20so%20we%20actually%20did%20see%20an%20influx%20of%20people%20moving%20to%20Canada%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tiffany%20Woodfield%2C%20a%20senior%20financial%20advisor%20at%20SWAN%20Wealth%20Management%20of%20Raymond%20James.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%2C%20especially%20across%20borders%2C%20is%20a%20big%20decision%20and%20shouldn't%20be%20taken%20lightly.%20While%20the%20physical%20act%20of%20moving%20is%20complicated%20enough%2C%20Woodfield%20points%20out%20that%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20financial%20considerations%20to%20be%20aware%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20sometimes%20it%20can%20be%20a%20knee-jerk%20reaction%2C%26quot%3B%20Woodfield%20said%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwe-moved-to-canada-not-perfect-but-prefer-over-us-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20to%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20don't%20plan%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20they%20can%20fall%20into%20traps%20that%20end%20up%20costing%20them%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4feab40-7084-4563-951b-72a890ad2b58%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20need%20to%20file%20US%20and%20Canadian%20taxes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20citizens%20residing%20in%20Canada%20might%20not%20realize%20that%20even%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20border%2C%20they're%20still%20not%20free%20from%20their%20tax%20obligations%20to%20Uncle%20Sam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20a%20US%20citizen%2C%20you%20still%20need%20to%20file%20federal%20US%20taxes%20and%20report%20your%20worldwide%20income%20to%20the%20IRS%20no%20matter%20where%20you%20live.%20In%20Canada%2C%20taxes%20are%20based%20on%20your%20residency%20status%2C%20so%20if%20you%20spend%20more%20than%20183%20days%20of%20the%20year%20living%20in%20Canada%2C%20you%20owe%20the%20Canadian%20government%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20ex-pats%20from%20getting%20taxed%20twice%20on%20their%20income%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20have%20a%20tax%20treaty%20that%20provides%20a%20foreign%20income%20tax%20credit%20for%20any%20income%20tax%20paid%20to%20the%20other%20country%2C%20Woodfield%20explained.%20That%20means%20you%20can%20offset%20your%20US%20tax%20liability%20with%20taxes%20already%20paid%20to%20Canada%2C%20but%20you%20still%20need%20to%20file%20two%20separate%20tax%20returns%20%E2%80%94%20one%20to%20Canada%20and%20one%20to%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20to%20receive%20a%20tax%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20promise%20of%20free%20healthcare%20in%20Canada%20might%20sound%20enticing%2C%20but%20that%20does%20come%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20higher%20taxes%2C%20so%20be%20aware%20that%20your%20Canadian%20tax%20bill%20will%20probably%20be%20higher%20than%20what%20you%20paid%20in%20the%20US.%20You%20also%20don't%20have%20the%20option%20to%20file%20joint%20income%20tax%20returns%20with%20your%20spouse%20in%20Canada%2C%20Woodfield%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227d31b42f-84db-43c3-b2f8-4f871c9958bf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20Canadian%20investments%20have%20complicated%20tax%20implications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20US%20person%20living%20in%20Canada%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20invest%20in%20Canadian%20mutual%20funds%20or%20Canadian%20ETFs%2C%26quot%3B%20Woodfield%20said.%20That's%20because%20these%20investments%20are%20considered%20Passive%20Foreign%20Income%20Corporations%20(PFIC)%20by%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPFICs%20are%20subject%20to%20unfavorable%20tax%20treatment%20from%20the%20IRS.%20The%20associated%20tax%20forms%20are%20lengthy%20and%20complicated%2C%20and%20you%20may%20end%20up%20paying%20high%20tax%20rates.%20If%20you're%20still%20a%20US%20citizen%2C%20investing%20in%20a%20Canadian%20mutual%20fund%20or%20ETF%20simply%20isn't%20worth%20the%20hassle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220333acc5-88aa-436b-bf74-7cb1b79b71b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBringing%20your%20retirement%20plan%20over%20the%20border%20can%20be%20tricky.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E401(k)s%20are%20a%20popular%20way%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%20here%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20Canadian%20employers%20offer%20a%20different%20type%20of%20retirement%20plan%3A%20the%20Registered%20Retirement%20Savings%20Plan%20(RRSP).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20move%20to%20Canada%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20actively%20manage%20the%20holdings%20in%20your%20401(k)%2C%20according%20to%20Woodfield.%20One%20workaround%20is%20to%20roll%20your%20401(k)%20to%20an%20IRA%20and%20have%20it%20managed%20in%20Canada.%20US%20citizens%20should%20also%20be%20aware%20that%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20they%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20contribute%20to%20their%20IRA%20once%20they%20move%20to%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20option%20is%20to%20transfer%20your%20US%20retirement%20account%20into%20an%20RRSP.%20However%2C%20if%20you%20choose%20this%20step%2C%20make%20sure%20you're%20committed%20to%20moving%20to%20Canada%20permanently%2C%20as%20you%20cannot%20move%20RRSPs%20to%20IRAs%2C%20Woodfield%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20bring%20your%20brokerage%20accounts%20over%20the%20border%2C%20either.%20Some%20people%20don't%20realize%20this%20until%20they%20update%20their%20address%20with%20their%20US%20brokerage%20account%20after%20moving%20and%20receive%20a%20letter%20informing%20them%20that%20they%20have%20to%20close%20out%20their%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d468c1f-efc0-45a8-9a7c-53c03c550ff1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou'll%20need%20a%20new%20financial%20advisor%E2%80%A6and%20a%20lot%20of%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20financial%20advisors%20are%20prohibited%20by%20law%20from%20providing%20Canadian%20residents%20with%20financial%20advice%2C%20as%20they%20aren't%20licensed%20in%20Canada.%20If%20you%20want%20expert%20advice%2C%20you%20need%20to%20work%20with%20a%20dual%20Canada%20%2F%20US%20licensed%20advisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20you%20start%20preparing%20for%20your%20cross-border%20move%2C%20the%20better%20%E2%80%94%20ideally%2C%20one%20to%20two%20tax%20years%20before%20moving%2C%20Woodfield%20said.%20That%20way%2C%20you%20can%20plan%20certain%20taxable%20events%20ahead%20of%20time%20and%20realize%20the%20greatest%20amount%20of%20savings%2C%20such%20as%20liquidating%20mutual%20funds.%20It's%20also%20easier%20to%20sell%20your%20home%20while%20you're%20still%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Woodfield%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20already%20begun%20the%20moving%20process%20or%20you're%20already%20in%20Canada%2C%20don't%20panic.%20Woodfield%20has%20worked%20with%20plenty%20of%20people%20after%20they've%20already%20moved%2C%20but%20the%20more%20time%20you%20give%20yourself%2C%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20across%20the%20border%20is%20no%20simple%20feat%2C%20so%20make%20sure%20you're%20confident%20about%20your%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20had%20clients%20that%20have%20moved%2C%20and%20then%20after%20the%20fact%2C%20they%20think%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20shouldn't%20have%20done%20this%2C'%26quot%3B%20Woodfield%20said.%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20hard%20to%20go%20back%2C%20so%20people%20need%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-canada-from-america-tax-investment-implications-election-trump-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731756781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67361df5192f52589858809c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-canada-from-america-tax-investment-implications-election-trump-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Interest%20in%20moving%20to%20Canada%20has%20spiked%20among%20Americans.%20Financial%20advisor%20Tiffany%20Woodfield%20shares%204%20ways%20it'll%20impact%20your%20finances.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cji%40businessinsider.com%20(Christine%20Ji)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-canada-from-america-tax-investment-implications-election-trump-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ranveer%20says%20life%20with%20daughter%20Dua%20is%20infinite%20happiness%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731756774000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-115361088%2Cimgsize-47150.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Franveer-singh-says-life-with-daughter-dua-singh-is-infinite-happiness-showers-praise-on-wife-deepika-padukone-watch%2Farticleshow%2F115361088.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F115361088.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EBollywood%20couple%20Deepika%20Padukone%20and%20Ranveer