licans%20to%20help%20him%20use%20a%20special%20procedure%20called%20recess%20appointments%20that%20would%20allow%20him%20to%20install%20Cabinet%20appointees%20and%20even%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%20without%20a%20single%20vote.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20theory%2C%20Trump's%20push%20for%20broad%20recess%20appointment%20power%20could%20allow%20him%20to%20disregard%20the%20process%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20any%20more%20than%201%2C200%20positions%20requiring%20Senate%20confirmation%20could%20be%20filled%20without%20even%20an%20FBI%20background%20check%20or%20a%20confirmation%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20been%20made%20so%20explicit%20and%20used%20as%20a%20strategy%20in%20and%20of%20itself%20that%20even%20though%20former%20presidents%20made%20recess%20appointments%2C%20they%20didn't%20say%20this%20part%2C%20and%20there%20wasn't%20widespread%20fear%20about%20what%20it%20means%20and%20why%20they%20are%20using%20it%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Casey%20Burgat%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Affairs%20Program%20at%20George%20Washington%20University's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Political%20Management%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Trump%2C%20Musk%20is%20a%20big%20believer%20in%20flexing%20the%20recess%20appointment%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20richest%20man%20recently%20wrote%20on%20X%20that%20without%20them%2C%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20to%20enact%20the%20change%20demanded%20by%20the%20American%20people%2C%20which%20is%20utterly%20unacceptable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20John%20Thune%20of%20South%20Dakota%2C%20who%20won%20the%20race%20to%20replace%20Sen.%20Mitch%20McConnell%20of%20Kentucky%2C%20has%20said%20%26quot%3Ball%20options%20are%20on%20the%20table%2C%20including%20recess%20appointments.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20Thune%20stressed%20that%20Trump%20may%20still%20encounter%20obstacles%20if%20he%20goes%20that%20route.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20have%20all%20Republicans%20vote%20to%20recess%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Thune%20told%20Fox%20News%20host%20Bret%20Baier.%20%26quot%3BThe%20same%20Republicans%20that%20you%20mentioned%20that%20might%20have%20a%20problem%20voting%20for%20somebody%20under%20regular%20order%20might%20be%20the%20same%20Republicans%20that%20have%20a%20problem%20voting%20to%20put%20the%20Senate%20into%20recess.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229fdd85ec-762d-4f4e-9d55-9d0cd426582d%5C%22%3EWhy%20Trump%20wants%20this%20power.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20could%20get%20his%20choices%20confirmed%20with%20just%2050%20votes%2C%20thanks%20to%20Vice%20President-elect%20JD%20Vance's%20tie-breaking%20power.%20With%20Republicans%20projected%20to%20hold%2053%20seats%2C%20Democrats%20can't%20stop%20a%20nomination%20on%20their%20own.%20But%20they%20can%20force%20Republicans%20to%20grind%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20push%20for%20recess%20appointment%20power%2C%20Trump%20argued%20it%20was%20about%20ensuring%20he%20could%20staff%20up%20in%20a%20timely%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Center%20for%20Presidential%20Transition%2C%20it%20took%20President%20Trump%20twice%20as%20long%20on%20average%20to%20get%20his%20nominees%20approved%20during%20his%20first%20three%20years%20in%20office%20(115%20days)%20than%20it%20did%20Ronald%20Reagan's%20presidency%20(56.4)%20days.%20Through%20late%20November%202023%2C%20it%20took%20President%20Biden%20roughly%20109.6%20days%20on%20average.%20The%20center%20also%20found%20that%20while%20the%20Senate%20filibuster%20is%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20for%20delays%2C%20even%20complete%20control%20of%20Congress%20hasn't%20sped%20things%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20convinced%20that%20time%20is%20Trump's%20sole%20motivation%2C%20particularly%20when%20many%20of%20his%20early%20selections%20illustrate%20how%20much%20he%20will%20elevate%20controversial%20choices%20like%20Gaetz%20and%20Kennedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20the%20president's%20perspective%2C%20I%20suppose%20he%20would%20see%20this%20as%20a%20shortcut%20to%20take%20his%20favorite%20list%20of%20appointees%20and%20put%20them%20in%20for%20temporary%20appointments%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarah%20Binder%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20Brookings%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22745efdee-399a-4d58-9336-c1b7209a287e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20can't%20flex%20this%20power%20by%20himself.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Thune%20said%2C%20the%20Senate%20would%20need%20to%20vote%20on%20adjournment.%20The%20Constitution%20also%20requires%20the%20House%20to%20approve%20the%20Senate%20breaking%20for%20over%20three%20days.%20A%202014%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20held%20that%20the%20Senate%20would%20need%20to%20recess%20for%20at%20least%2010%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20even%20a%20way%20for%20Trump%20to%20avoid%20the%20House's%20need%20to%20sign%20off%20on%20a%20lengthy%20break.%20Under%20Article%20II%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20Trump%20has%20the%20power%20to%20force%20an%20adjournment%20if%20the%20House%20and%20Senate%20are%20divided%20on%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20is%20the%20only%20true%20limit%20on%20recess%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20installed%20via%20recess%20appointment%20can%20only%20serve%20until%20Congress'%20next%20session.%20If%20Trump%20uses%20this%20power%20immediately%20upon%20taking%20office%2C%20officials%20or%20judges%20could%20only%20stay%20through%20the%20next%20Senate%20session%2C%20in%20January%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOtherwise%2C%20there%20is%20virtually%20nothing%20Senate%20Democrats%20could%20do%20to%20stop%20the%20process.%20Adjournment%20votes%20can't%20be%20meaningfully%20filibustered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b23bbc27-f0ff-4ab9-95b7-d757a9914d9d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecess%20appointments%20were%20created%20for%20a%20bygone-era.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20World%20War%20II%2C%20presidents%20needed%20recess%20appointment%20power%20because%20the%20US%20Senate%20was%20out%20of%20session%20more%20often%20than%20lawmakers%20were%20in%20the%20nation's%20capital.%20Presidents%20sometimes%20used%20their%20power%20to%20game%20the%20system%2C%20rushing%20nominees%20through%20who%20might%20have%20failed%20to%20get%20confirmed.%20In%202005%2C%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%20bypassed%20the%20senate%20to%20appoint%20John%20Bolton%20as%20Ambassador%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20over%20criticism%20from%20Senate%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20senators%2C%20including%20Republicans%2C%20have%20tried%20to%20thwart%20presidents%20from%20using%20their%20recess%20appointment%20power%20by%20holding%20%26quot%3Bpro-forma%26quot%3B%20sessions%20where%20even%20just%20one%20senator%20can%20briefly%20convene%20and%20conclude%20business%20within%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c5b5cf7b-d42b-4d24-931f-6e4885ad0309%5C%22%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20convinced%20this%20power%20grab%20is%20wise.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20biggest%20defender%20thus%20far%20is%20former%20White%20House%20counsel%20Don%20McGahn.%20In%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20op-ed%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20McGahn%20said%20that%20Trump%20needs%20the%20power%20because%20the%20Senate%20is%20too%20slow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReturning%20to%20the%20longstanding%20tradition%20of%20recess%20appointments%20would%20ensure%20that%20every%20elected%20president%20is%20able%20to%20staff%20the%20government%20with%20senior%20officials%20who%20share%20his%20policy%20vision%2C%26quot%3B%20McGahn%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20conservatives%20are%20skeptical.%20Ed%20Whelan%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Ethics%20and%20Public%20Policy%20Center%2C%20a%20conservative%20think%20tank%2C%20strongly%20opposes%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20show%20that%20you're%20fundamentally%20hostile%20to%20the%20constitutional%20separation%20of%20powers%2C%20trying%20to%20do%20a%20blanket%20bypass%20of%20Senate's%20core%20advice-and-consent%20authority%20is%20a%20good%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Whelan%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Review%20wrote%20in%20a%20Wednesday%20editorial%20that%20Trump's%20request%20is%20%26quot%3Bwholly%20inappropriate%20within%20the%20American%20system%20of%20government%20and%20ought%20to%20be%20rejected%20with%20prejudice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20may%20only%20be%20in%20power%20for%20four%20years%2C%20but%20the%20reality%20of%20Washington%20is%20that%20if%20he%20follows%20Musk's%20encouragement%2C%20he%20will%20set%20a%20standard%20Republicans%20will%20one%20day%20regret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Senate%20works%20on%20precedent%2C%20and%20so%20whatever%20happened%20last%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20default%20for%20how%20it%20should%20happen%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Burgat%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20so%20if%20we%20know%20anything%20about%20politics%20and%20power%20grabs%20they%20are%20really%20hard%20to%20claw%20back%20and%20the%20next%20guy%20is%20gonna%20use%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-recess-appointments-musk-trump-cabinet-senate-explainer-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731754981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6733705c88cea3ba1c201a82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-recess-appointments-musk-trump-cabinet-senate-explainer-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20is%20pushing%20Senate%20Republicans%20to%20give%20him%20more%20power%20to%20fill%20offices%20without%20Senate%20approval%20via%20recess%20appointments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-recess-appointments-musk-trump-cabinet-